for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students","content":"这是一篇译文，原文为 Stephen Wu 于 2024 年 9 月发表的 Advice for students。Stephen\n曾经在 Facebook 工作，现为 Notion 数据库团队的软件工程师。我在推特偶然看到他的主页并读到此文，深受启发，遂翻译分享。**以下正文中的「我」均指原作者 Stephen Wu**，如有歧义请以原文为准。"},"15":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-13","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students","content":"**一些适合学生的通用建议**"},"16":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-14","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students","content":"这些建议主要面向那些对在现代科技公司担任技术岗位感兴趣的计算机专业大学生，不过，其中很多内容对其他人也同样适用。"},"17":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-15","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students","content":"常见的技术岗位有：软件工程师、产品经理、数据科学家、数据工程师或产品设计师等。"},"18":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-16","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"**我对学生们的一贯建议可以总结为以下几点：**"},"19":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-17","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"探索生命的意义（ikigai），并寻求目标与内心的一致性。"},"20":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-18","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"打好心理与身体健康的基础。"},"21":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-19","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"开展你热爱的课余项目，并与志同道合的伙伴一起完成。"},"22":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-20","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"在职业发展上做出「明智的」投入。"},"23":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-21","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"让阅读成为一种习惯，也成为一种热爱。"},"24":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-22","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"不要像 NPC 那样随波逐流、缺乏思考！"},"25":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-23","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"**关于建议的一点说明**"},"26":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-24","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"建议总是依赖于特定语境，也往往是简化的表达，因此并不一定适用于每个人。"},"27":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-25","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"接纳那些与你产生共鸣的建议，并时常回顾；无法产生共鸣的也无需强求。"},"28":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-26","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#通用建议","content":"多接触不同的资源，广泛阅读各种想法！"},"29":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-27","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"人们常用这样一幅维恩图来形象地解释 ikigai（存在的意义）："},"30":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-28","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"找到你的 ikigai，意味着找到你热爱的事、你擅长的事、这个世界需要的事、以及能为你带来收入的事，这四者的交集。"},"31":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-29","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"你热爱的事：是那些你在从事时感到真正的乐趣与激情的工作。"},"32":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-30","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"你能获得报酬的事：是那些能为你带来外在回报，有助于生活与财务的工作。"},"33":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-31","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"你擅长的事：你的技能与这类工作高度契合，而且你也有持续提升的兴趣。"},"34":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-32","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"这个世界需要的事：你能为他人创造价值，并感受到自己正在为社会或社群做出贡献。"},"35":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-33","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"在我与人们探讨职业满足感时，我发现最快乐的人，往往在这四个方面都达到了很高的程度。"},"36":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-34","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"你也可以从另一个角度思考：寻找那些既能激发你内在热情，又能带来外在回报的机会。\n在职业生涯的早期阶段，你也许更应该关注**成长空间**和**学习潜力**。"},"37":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-35","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"通常来说，那些兼具内外动机的事情——既让你发自内心地热爱，又带来现实回报——你越有动力去做好，它们成功的可能性也越大。"},"38":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-36","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"**举几个例子：**"},"39":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-37","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我在做一个我热爱的课余项目，它很有意义，同时还能帮助我学习 React。"},"40":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-38","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我正在实习，这份工作一方面帮我赚取学费，另一方面让我学到不少新东西。"},"41":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-39","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我花时间和我很敬佩的人相处，从他们身上学到很多。"},"42":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-40","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"我的工作把我热爱的艺术与设计结合在一起，比如在 Figma 这样的公司工作。"},"43":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-41","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#ikigai存在的意义","content":"**理想情况下，几年后你可以达到这样的状态：**"},"44":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-42","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags"