#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"d. 做游戏 → 用 Godot"},"97":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-95","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"给自己设定一到多个具体目标"},"98":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-96","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"a. “我想尝试用 React 做一个全栈应用！”"},"99":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-97","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"b. “我想发布一个作品并放进我的作品集网站！”"},"100":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-98","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"c. “我想做个东西帮我更高效地锻炼。”"},"101":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-99","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"d. “我想学会使用 Cursor IDE。”"},"102":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-100","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"如果可以，找一些一起做项目的伙伴"},"103":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-101","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"a. 可以是一起参与项目，也可以是找人一起 co-work，各自做各自的项目但彼此分享进展、互相监督。"},"104":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-102","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"b. 很多高校都有这类社团或俱乐部可以加入！"},"105":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-103","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"真正为这个项目留出时间，并持续投入下去"},"106":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-104","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"不用追求完美！重点是多动手去做。只要你构建了点什么，就已经成功了一步！项目完成后，别忘了把它放到 GitHub、简历、个人网站或者 YouTube 上。它就成了你能力的一个具体作品，别人能直接看到和理解。"},"107":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-105","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#开展你热爱的课余项目","content":"我大学时也做过一些这样的项目，有些不过是几个周末的尝试。"},"108":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-106","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"一般来说，有助于职业发展的活动包括，但不限于："},"109":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-107","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"简历润色与简历互评"},"110":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-108","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"参考：https\\://careercup.com/resume ——那里有很好的建议"},"111":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-109","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"课余/个人项目"},"112":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-110","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"校园招聘会"},"113":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-111","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"「打造社交网络」（拓宽职业人脉）"},"114":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-112","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"学习如何与业界人士交流"},"115":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-113","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"面试与模拟面试"},"116":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-114","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"《Cracking the Coding Interview》这本书仍然很有价值且实用"},"117":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-115","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"我不打算逐条详细解释，但要理解以下几点很重要："},"118":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-116","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"**无论如何，你都需要投入一定的时间和精力，而投入的多少取决于你想达到的目标高度。**"},"119":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-117","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"光有一纸大学文凭，工作不会自己送上门来。"},"120":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-118","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"像 Google、Facebook 这样的公司，每年都会收到数以百万计的求职申请。"},"121":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-119","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"如果一家公司只录取 10% 的申请人，你的「求职资料包」就得胜过剩下 90% 的人。"},"122":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-120","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"很多时候，质量比数量更重要。"},"123":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-121","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"你可能海投 400 份简历，却依然毫无进展。"},"124":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-122","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"很多时候，通过招聘会建立的正确人脉、找到合适的岗位、做出有分量的副业项目、发出恰到好处的一条推文，或者获得前同事的推荐，这些途径的效果都比海投简历高出百倍。"},"125":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-123","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"充分准备是关键。"},"126":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-124","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"了解面试的流程并进行练习，提前准备好向面试官提的问题，以及一些交流要点——都能让你的面试通过率大幅提升。"},"127":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-125","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"如果求职流程的某个环节出了问题，就要评估并改进它。"},"128":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-126","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"比如，你申请了很多公司却完全没有收到面试通知，那么你的简历可能比其他候选人竞争力弱，或者你投递的渠道本身质量很差。"},"129":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-127","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#把精力花在对职业有帮助的事上","content":"又比如，你的面试总是没通过，那你可能需要多做模拟面试，并复盘分析自己没通过的原因。"},"130":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-128","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"我认为阅读是你一生中能做的最重要的事情之一。"},"131":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-129","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"我个人非常喜欢非虚构类书籍和回忆录！"},"132":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-130","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"关于非虚构，有一种让我深有共鸣的切入点是："},"133":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-131","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"那些拥有你渴望掌握的技能、思想和知识的人，往往花费了无数时间，把他们最重要的体会和智慧，浓缩成一本经过精心打磨、广受好评的书。而这些书籍，已经被许多人证明确实能带来帮助。"},"134":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-132","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"有句话说：“你会越来越像与你相处的人。”——阅读一本好书，其实就是在与那些优秀而有趣的人对话，进入他们的思维世界。这是一个宝贵的机会，让你在没有师长陪伴时，也能从最值得学习的人那里汲取养分。"},"135":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-133","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"在这里推荐一些书籍："},"136":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-134","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"《原子习惯》通常是非虚构阅读的一个好入门，因为它能帮助你建立起关于习惯、环境和激励机制的思维模型，从而进一步培养更强的阅读习惯。"},"137":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-135","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"《程序员修炼之道》是关于编程最优秀的著作之一。"},"138":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-136","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"《数据密集型应用系统设计》是系统设计中最著名的书籍之一，非常适合倾向后端方向的工程师（坦白说我自己没读过）。"},"139":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-137","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"《被讨厌的勇气》是阿德勒哲学的一个很好的入门。"},"140":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-138","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"《算法之美》能帮助你把计算机科学的思维与现实生活的系统和决策联系起来。"},"141":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-139","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"回忆录推荐：《绿灯》（马修·麦康纳海）、《人类世回顾》（约翰·格林）、《也许你该找个人聊聊》（洛莉·戈特利布）。"},"142":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-140","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"偶尔随意浏览 HackerNews 或 Twitter 上的科技内容，也会既有趣又有收获。"},"143":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-141","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"推荐的 Substack：Astral Codex Ten、bookbear、The Pragmatic Engineer、Escaping Flatland。"},"144":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-142","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"一些阅读建议："},"145":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-143","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"阅读非虚构时，最好处于一种特定的心态：你对该主题感兴趣、保持开放心态并且充满好奇。"},"146":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-144","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"有时某本书在你当前的状态下可能不会引起共鸣，这没关系——你随时可以在以后再读。"},"147":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-145","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"你完全没必要一次只读一本书。如果此刻对某本书没兴趣，可以先放下，等以后再拿起来。"},"148":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-146","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"小说最好一次读一本，以免情节和细节混淆。"},"149":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-147","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"非虚构则无所谓，即便几个月后再继续读也可以。你还可以跳读、非线性阅读，因为许多要点其实会被反复提到。"},"150":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-148","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"一定要做标注！并把精彩的引语或笔记记录在 Kindle、Notion 或 Readwise 里。"},"151":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-149","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#building-a-habit-and-love-of-reading","content":"时间和注意力都是有限的资源——而现在我们很容易在社交媒体或信息流里一刷就是好几个小时。（我自己会用 One Sec 这个应用来提醒和控制）\n如果能把其中一部分时间换成阅读，你会发现这对生活真的很有益 🙂。"},"152":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-150","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"**要学会培养自己的主动性。**"},"153":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-151","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"所谓主动性，大致可以理解为：你有能力根据自己的目标采取行动，并影响自己和周围的环境。"},"154":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-152","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"一个粗略的比喻是——“不要当游戏里的 NPC”。"},"155":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-153","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"作为玩家角色，你可以根据自己的信念、价值观和目标走出属于自己的道路。如果你的目标是通关游戏，你就可以去尝试；如果你想完成一条支线任务，你也完全可以去做。"},"156":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-154","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"而作为非玩家角色（NPC），你只能被动接受外界的摆布，受到既定程序和路线的限制。NPC 的生活就像是在说：“唉，这就是我所处的世界，这就是我被发到的牌。”"},"157":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-155","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"在当下，“NPC”这个说法的 Z 世代版本，大概就是所谓的“主角气场（main character energy）”，它有时是褒义，有时是贬义。另外，还有一种流行的趋势叫“显化（manifestation）”，虽然听上去像是“灵修玄学”，但我觉得其中确实有一些值得参考的东西。"},"158":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-156","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"我认为，培养主动性很大一部分在于逐渐改变你对自己的叙事：你能做什么，你的限制是什么，你的未来会怎样。另一部分则是：你真的去做那些你想做的事。"},"159":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-157","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"这可能意味着，你需要把自己的想法拿出来，找出那些你反复告诉自己的限制，然后去想办法突破它们。比如："},"160":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-158","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"“我不是一个好学生 / 我不够聪明 / 我没有足够的成就和野心。”"},"161":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-159","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"“我很懒 / 我精力不如别人。”"},"162":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-160","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"“我开始学编程太晚了 / 我什么都不懂 / 别人比我更适合这个领域。”"},"163":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-161","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"“事情就是这样 / 我就是这样 / 未来也不会有改变。”"},"164":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-162","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"这些被你不断暗示的限制，最终会形成自我实现的预言，塑造你的身份认同。"},"165":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-163","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"当然，并不是所有限制都能被克服，但很多限制其实主要来自你自己讲给自己的故事，以及你自己制造的惯性。"},"166":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-164","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#不要做一个npc","content":"在实践层面，这可能意味着：写日记、冥想、心理咨询、给自己一些积极的提醒，或者重复一些正面的信念。也可以多和朋友谈谈问题，互相帮助、共同解决。🙂"},"167":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-165","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#other-relevant-quotes-captured-by-much-better-writers","content":"摘自 Ava 的 《Actually Everyone’s Life is Weird》:"},"168":{"id":"/notes/advice-for-students-166","page_id":"/notes/advice-for-students","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/advice-for-students#other-relevant-quotes-captured-by-much-better-writers","content":"> 我真希望小时候有人告诉我，关于工作的唯一真正‘规则’，其实就是：你要能支付房租、不伤害别人、不违法。只要符合这三点，你几乎可以去做任何事情，最好是能让自己觉得有意义的事。世界本来就是如此美妙、开放、而且奇妙的。\n>\n> 我成长的环境却让我觉得，如果成绩单上哪怕只有一个 B+，我的人生就完了——没有大学会录取我，我也永远进不了所谓的 FAANG 大厂，最后只能孤独终老。这样的逻辑让我很努力，但同时也让我变得焦虑和恐惧，这些心结花了我很久才慢慢解开。\n>\n> 现在我相信，如果你有创造力，并且愿意努力工作，其实有很多不同的道路都能通向成功。"},"169":{"id":"/notes/alipayhk","page_id":"/notes/alipayhk","type":"page","content":"AlipayHK","breadcrumbs":["Docs"],"tags":[],"url":"/notes/alipayhk"},"170":{"id":"/notes/alipayhk-0","page_id":"/notes/alipayhk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/alipayhk","content":"AlipayHK（支付宝香港）是支付宝为香港市场推出的本地化版本。"},"171":{"id":"/notes/alipayhk-1","page_id":"/notes/alipayhk","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/alipayhk#前置准备","content":"前置准备"},"172":{"id":"/notes/alipayhk-2","page_id":"/notes/alipayhk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/alipayhk#前置准备","content":"国区 Apple ID"},"173":{"id":"/notes/alipayhk-3","page_id":"/notes/alipayhk","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/alipayhk#前置准备","content":"AlipayHK 是支付宝为香港市场推出的本地化版本，不过大陆用户也可以在国区应用商店中下载。"},"174":{"id":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks","page_id":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks","type":"page","content":"Formbricks 配置 Caddy 反代","breadcrumbs":["Docs"],"tags":[],"url":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks"},"175":{"id":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks-0","page_id":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks","content":"已经启动了 Formbricks 的 Docker 容器，可以通过公网访问 IP:3000"},"176":{"id":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks-1","page_id":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/caddy-and-formbricks","content":"但是我想实现 survey.ztm0929.cn 的域名访问。"},"177":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","type":"page","content":"中国法律位阶","breadcrumbs":["Docs"],"tags":[],"url":"/notes/chinese-law"},"178":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-0","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law","content":"对中国法律位阶的概述"},"179":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-1","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/chinese-law#参考资料","content":"参考资料"},"180":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-2","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law","content":"中国大陆的法律体系，按照效力位阶，可大致分为以下几个层级：宪法、法律、行政法规、地方性法规、规章。宪法是根本大法，具有最高的法律效力，其他法律都不能与宪法相抵触。\n以下是具体层级及其制定机关："},"181":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-3","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law","content":"宪法:\n《中华人民共和国宪法》是国家的根本大法，是其他一切法律的立法依据和基础。"},"182":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-4","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law","content":"法律:\n由全国人民代表大会(全国人大)及其常务委员会制定，如《中华人民共和国民法典》、《中华人民共和国刑法》等。"},"183":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-5","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law","content":"行政法规:\n由国务院制定，是对法律的具体化和补充，如《中华人民共和国食品安全法实施条例》。"},"184":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-6","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law","content":"地方性法规:\n由省级和设区的市级人民代表大会及其常务委员会制定，在各自的行政区域内施行，如《上海市生活垃圾管理条例》。"},"185":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-7","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law","content":"规章:\n包括部门规章和地方政府规章，部门规章由国务院各部委制定，地方政府规章由地方各级人民政府制定。\n此外，还有一些特殊类型的法律，如自治条例和单行条例，它们在民族自治地方和经济特区具有特殊法律地位。法律效力层级的高低，决定了在具体适用法律时的优先顺序，下位法必须服从上位法。"},"186":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-8","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law#参考资料","content":"中华人民共和国法律位阶 - 维基百科"},"187":{"id":"/notes/chinese-law-9","page_id":"/notes/chinese-law","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/chinese-law#参考资料","content":"法律位阶 - 百度百科"},"188":{"id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy","page_id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy","type":"page","content":"部署 FreshRSS","breadcrumbs":["Docs"],"tags":[],"url":"/notes/freshrss-deploy"},"189":{"id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy-0","page_id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/freshrss-deploy","content":"FreshRSS 是一个自托管的 RSS 阅读器。"},"190":{"id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy-1","page_id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/notes/freshrss-deploy#docker-部署-freshrss","content":"Docker 部署 FreshRSS"},"191":{"id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy-2","page_id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/freshrss-deploy","content":"https\\://freshrss.org/"},"192":{"id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy-3","page_id":"/notes/freshrss-deploy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/notes/fr